# Authentication & Authorization Rules

## Overview
This application uses **Supabase Auth** exclusively for authentication. NextAuth is disabled and should not be used.

## Authentication Architecture

### 1. Supabase Auth Configuration
```typescript
// ✅ Always use Supabase helpers in lib/supabase.ts
//  • createClient()  – browser/client components (uses createBrowserClient)
//  • createServerClient(cookieStore) – server components / API routes (uses createServerClient)

import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase'   // <- browser
import { createServerClient } from '@/lib/supabase' // <- server

// Browser usage
const supabase = createClient()

// Server usage
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'
const supabaseServer = createServerClient(cookies())
```

### 2. Environment Variables
```env
# ✅ Required - Only use anon key, never service role key in client
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
```

## Authentication Patterns

### 1. Client-Side Authentication
```typescript
// ✅ Sign up pattern
const handleSignUp = async (email: string, password: string) => {
  const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.signUp({
    email,
    password,
    options: {
      emailRedirectTo: `${window.location.origin}/auth/callback`
    }
  })
  
  if (error) {
    throw new Error(error.message)
  }
  
  return data
}

// ✅ Sign in pattern
const handleSignIn = async (email: string, password: string) => {
  const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.signInWithPassword({
    email,
    password
  })
  
  if (error) {
    throw new Error(error.message)
  }
  
  return data
}

// ✅ Sign out pattern
const handleSignOut = async () => {
  const { error } = await supabase.auth.signOut()
  if (error) {
    console.error('Sign out error:', error)
  }
}
```

### 2. Server-Side Authentication
```typescript
// ✅ Use auth helpers from lib/auth.ts
import { getServerSession, requireAuth } from '@/lib/auth'

// For optional authentication
const sessionData = await getServerSession()
if (sessionData) {
  const { user, session } = sessionData
  // Handle authenticated user
}

// For required authentication (redirects if not authenticated)
const { user, session } = await requireAuth()
```

### 3. Client-Side Session Management
```typescript
// ✅ Use AuthProvider for session state
import { useAuth } from '@/components/auth-provider'

function Component() {
  const { user, loading, signOut } = useAuth()
  
  if (loading) return <div>Loading...</div>
  
  return user ? (
    <div>Welcome, {user.email}</div>
  ) : (
    <div>Please sign in</div>
  )
}
```

## Authorization Patterns

### 1. Role-Based Access Control
```typescript
// ✅ Use helper functions from lib/auth.ts
import { isAdmin, hasValidSubscription } from '@/lib/auth'

// Check admin status
if (isAdmin(user)) {
  // Admin-only functionality
}

// Check subscription status
if (hasValidSubscription(user)) {
  // Premium features
}
```

### 2. User Roles
```typescript
// ✅ Supported roles (lower-case strings)
type UserRole = 'user' | 'admin'

// Role assignment in user metadata
const user: AuthUser = {
  ...session.user,
  role: session.user.user_metadata?.role || 'USER'
}

```

### 4.1 Hydrate AuthProvider to avoid auth “flash”

Send the current session from the *server component* (e.g. `app/layout.tsx`) into `AuthProvider` so the header renders with the correct user immediately.

#### Root layout pattern
```tsx
import { getServerSession } from '@/lib/auth'
import { Providers } from '@/components/providers'

export default async function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  const sessionData = await getServerSession()
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        <Providers
          initialUser={sessionData?.user}
          initialSession={sessionData?.session}
        >
          {children}
        </Providers>
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

#### AuthProvider signature
```tsx
export function AuthProvider({ children, initialUser = null, initialSession = null }) {
  const [user, setUser] = useState(initialUser)
  const [session, setSession] = useState(initialSession)
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(!initialSession)
  ...
}
```

With this pattern the first paint is already authenticated, eliminating the Sign-In / Get-Started flash on protected pages (`/my-products`, `/edit-product-stripe`).

## Route Protection

### 1. Middleware Protection
```typescript
// ✅ Protect routes with middleware
export async function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
  const supabase = createServerClient(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!,
    {
      cookies: {
        getAll() {
          return request.cookies.getAll()
        },
        setAll(cookiesToSet) {
          cookiesToSet.forEach(({ name, value, options }) => {
            response.cookies.set(name, value, options)
          })
        },
      },
    }
  )

  const { data: { session } } = await supabase.auth.getSession()
  
  const isProtectedRoute = request.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith('/dashboard')
  
  if (isProtectedRoute && !session) {
    const loginUrl = new URL('/login', request.url)
    loginUrl.searchParams.set('redirectTo', request.nextUrl.pathname)
    return NextResponse.redirect(loginUrl)
  }
}
```

### 2. Page-Level Protection
```typescript
// ✅ Protect pages with requireAuth
export default async function ProtectedPage() {
  const { user } = await requireAuth()
  
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Welcome, {user.email}!</h1>
      {/* Protected content */}
    </div>
  )
}
```

### 3. API Route Protection
```typescript
// ✅ Protect API routes
export async function GET(request: Request) {
  const sessionData = await getServerSession()
  
  if (!sessionData) {
    return new Response('Unauthorized', { status: 401 })
  }
  
  const { user } = sessionData
  
  // Handle authenticated request
  return Response.json({ user })
}
```

## Error Handling

### 1. Authentication Errors
```typescript
// ✅ Handle common auth errors
function handleAuthError(error: Error): string {
  if (error.message.includes('Invalid login credentials')) {
    return 'Invalid email or password'
  }
  if (error.message.includes('Email not confirmed')) {
    return 'Please check your email and click the confirmation link'
  }
  if (error.message.includes('Too many requests')) {
    return 'Too many attempts. Please try again later'
  }
  return 'An unexpected error occurred'
}
```

### 2. Session Errors
```typescript
// ✅ Handle session errors gracefully
try {
  const { data: { session } } = await supabase.auth.getSession()
  return session
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Session error:', error)
  return null
}
```

## Security Best Practices

### 1. Row Level Security (RLS)
```sql
-- ✅ Always enable RLS on user tables
ALTER TABLE user_profiles ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- ✅ Create policies for user data access
CREATE POLICY "Users can view own profile" ON user_profiles
  FOR SELECT USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

CREATE POLICY "Users can update own profile" ON user_profiles
  FOR UPDATE USING (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

### 2. Email Verification
```typescript
// ✅ Require email verification
const { data, error } = await supabase.auth.signUp({
  email,
  password,
  options: {
    emailRedirectTo: `${window.location.origin}/auth/callback`
  }
})
```

### 3. Password Requirements
```typescript
// ✅ Enforce strong passwords
const passwordSchema = z.string()
  .min(8, 'Password must be at least 8 characters')
  .regex(/^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\d)/, 'Password must contain uppercase, lowercase, and number')
```

